a wonderful organ to pump blood.

01:23:37.640 --> 01:23:40.970 align:middle line:84%
And they haven't discovered
Harvey's theory of circulation.

01:23:40.970 --> 01:23:41.970 align:middle line:90%
Ah, ha ha.

01:23:41.970 --> 01:23:43.190 align:middle line:84%
They're using the
heart as a metaphor.

01:23:43.190 --> 01:23:43.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

01:23:43.990 --> 01:23:45.428 align:middle line:84%
They're using heart
as a metaphor.

01:23:45.428 --> 01:23:46.970 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a very bad
metaphor, I think.

01:23:46.970 --> 01:23:48.920 align:middle line:84%
>> They're using the
lower right-hand corner,

01:23:48.920 --> 01:23:51.210 align:middle line:90%
the size of a thumb.

01:23:51.210 --> 01:23:52.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Are you kidding me?

01:23:52.740 --> 01:23:53.680 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

01:23:53.680 --> 01:23:54.660 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

01:23:54.660 --> 01:23:55.930 align:middle line:90%
>> It's the size of a thumb.

01:23:55.930 --> 01:23:56.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

01:23:56.730 --> 01:23:58.650 align:middle line:90%
>> It's called the Hridayam.

01:23:58.650 --> 01:23:59.860 align:middle line:90%
And it's right here.

01:23:59.860 --> 01:24:00.660 align:middle line:90%
>> It grows there?

01:24:00.660 --> 01:24:01.480 align:middle line:90%
>> It's right there.

01:24:01.480 --> 01:24:01.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Naturally?

01:24:01.850 --> 01:24:02.430 align:middle line:90%
>> It's there.

01:24:02.430 --> 01:24:03.230 align:middle line:90%
It's there.

01:24:03.230 --> 01:24:05.040 align:middle line:10%
It's not in a physical
manifestation.

01:24:05.040 --> 01:24:05.840 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, I see.

01:24:05.840 --> 01:24:07.110 align:middle line:90%
>> It's in a subtle form.

01:24:07.110 --> 01:24:08.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, how do you contact it?

01:24:08.610 --> 01:24:10.485 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you've got to
get better technology.

01:24:10.485 --> 01:24:14.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, see, man, better
than LSD and better than--

01:24:14.980 --> 01:24:17.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, in LSD, you saw all
that, but it went by so fast,

01:24:17.850 --> 01:24:21.460 align:middle line:84%
and you didn't have a
model, a conceptual model,

01:24:21.460 --> 01:24:24.500 align:middle line:84%
to say that it
just went through.

01:24:24.500 --> 01:24:27.655 align:middle line:84%
Because so much went through
every time I took acid.

01:24:27.655 --> 01:24:31.750 align:middle line:84%
It must be for you too, that
what we have conceptualized

01:24:31.750 --> 01:24:36.520 align:middle line:84%
is the tiniest trivia of
the edge of the whole thing.

01:24:36.520 --> 01:24:38.930 align:middle line:84%
And that's why dying seemed
so fascinating to me.

01:24:38.930 --> 01:24:39.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly, man.

01:24:39.730 --> 01:24:40.980 align:middle line:90%
>> Because you're going like--

01:24:40.980 --> 01:24:42.355 align:middle line:84%
[IMITATES WHOOSHING]
--like this.

01:24:42.355 --> 01:24:43.155 align:middle line:90%
>> You hope.

01:24:43.155 --> 01:24:44.050 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES]

01:24:44.050 --> 01:24:44.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Huh?

01:24:44.530 --> 01:24:45.505 align:middle line:90%
>> It may not be that way.

01:24:45.505 --> 01:24:45.850 align:middle line:90%
I hope it is.

01:24:45.850 --> 01:24:46.990 align:middle line:90%
It's got to be that way.

01:24:46.990 --> 01:24:47.790 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:24:47.790 --> 01:24:52.290 align:middle line:84%
>> (SINGING) You never know
what will be coming down.

01:24:52.290 --> 01:24:54.040 align:middle line:84%
>> Can you have dinner
with us afterwards?

01:24:54.040 --> 01:24:54.480 align:middle line:90%
>> I can't.

01:24:54.480 --> 01:24:56.140 align:middle line:84%
I gotta fly back
to San Francisco.

01:24:56.140 --> 01:24:57.050 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, god.

01:24:57.050 --> 01:24:59.640 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm working against
a deadline for a book,

01:24:59.640 --> 01:25:00.560 align:middle line:90%
a deadline.

01:25:00.560 --> 01:25:01.777 align:middle line:84%
>> You go work against
a deadline too.

01:25:01.777 --> 01:25:02.190 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

01:25:02.190 --> 01:25:02.960 align:middle line:90%
>> How about that deadline?

01:25:02.960 --> 01:25:03.180 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

01:25:03.180 --> 01:25:04.660 align:middle line:90%
>> Speaking of deadlines.

01:25:04.660 --> 01:25:07.380 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

01:25:07.380 --> 01:25:11.160 align:middle line:84%
>> Towards the end of May
1996, Leary began to show signs

01:25:11.160 --> 01:25:13.290 align:middle line:90%
of kidney and liver failure.

01:25:13.290 --> 01:25:15.930 align:middle line:84%
>> I think some of his fears of
letting go and not knowing what

01:25:15.930 --> 01:25:17.320 align:middle line:90%
was next--

01:25:17.320 --> 01:25:18.500 align:middle line:90%
I think that scared him.

01:25:18.500 --> 01:25:23.210 align:middle line:84%
And I think he was absolutely
normal and understandably human

01:25:23.210 --> 01:25:24.420 align:middle line:90%
in those moments.

01:25:24.420 --> 01:25:28.290 align:middle line:84%
But the process of dying
and actually slipping

01:25:28.290 --> 01:25:32.760 align:middle line:84%
into that unknown was
incredibly beautiful for him.

01:25:32.760 --> 01:25:37.110 align:middle line:84%
It was everybody else around
that was freaking out.

01:25:37.110 --> 01:25:40.560 align:middle line:84%
Ram Dass was really
mostly there for us.

01:25:40.560 --> 01:25:42.090 align:middle line:84%
It was the counseling
he was sort

01:25:42.090 --> 01:25:46.900 align:middle line:84%
of giving to us that was
so precious and meaningful.

01:25:46.900 --> 01:25:48.150 align:middle line:90%
It kind of got out of control.

01:25:48.150 --> 01:25:49.860 align:middle line:84%
We probably had too
many people around.

01:25:49.860 --> 01:25:51.780 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of us didn't
really know what we

01:25:51.780 --> 01:25:54.220 align:middle line:90%
were going to do once he died.

01:25:54.220 --> 01:25:58.170 align:middle line:84%
>> And so I was talking them
about not talking to him,

01:25:58.170 --> 01:26:01.800 align:middle line:84%
not trying to engage him,
not trying to pull him back,

01:26:01.800 --> 01:26:03.660 align:middle line:84%
but to let him be
wherever he is.

01:26:03.660 --> 01:26:05.210 align:middle line:84%
But they could talk
among themselves

01:26:05.210 --> 01:26:06.960 align:middle line:84%
in the room about all
the beautiful things

01:26:06.960 --> 01:26:11.360 align:middle line:84%
he'd done in life, which is
like an old Tibetan practice.

01:26:11.360 --> 01:26:15.360 align:middle line:84%
And I talked to them about
working on themselves

01:26:15.360 --> 01:26:18.450 align:middle line:84%
to not demand linearity,
so that, if he comes up

01:26:18.450 --> 01:26:21.180 align:middle line:84%
with things from different
places, to let their minds

01:26:21.180 --> 01:26:24.720 align:middle line:84%
soar so they could be with
him as his mind floated

01:26:24.720 --> 01:26:28.050 align:middle line:90%
through planes of consciousness.

01:26:28.050 --> 01:26:30.620 align:middle line:84%
And I told them to love death
as much as they love life,

01:26:30.620 --> 01:26:33.440 align:middle line:84%
to allow the mystery
of the universe

01:26:33.440 --> 01:26:37.770 align:middle line:84%
to be something
awesome and beautiful.

01:26:37.770 --> 01:26:40.350 align:middle line:90%
>> He was letting go willingly.

01:26:40.350 --> 01:26:43.020 align:middle line:84%
He wasn't trying to
just hang on, hang on,

01:26:43.020 --> 01:26:45.390 align:middle line:84%
even if the quality
of life suffered.

01:26:45.390 --> 01:26:49.740 align:middle line:84%
He was really going with the
organic nature of things.

01:26:49.740 --> 01:26:53.640 align:middle line:84%
>> We haven't really created
the right space for people not

01:26:53.640 --> 01:26:57.610 align:middle line:84%
to be afraid during this moment
that can be very frightening.

01:26:57.610 --> 01:27:00.560 align:middle line:84%
But as Tim Leary said,
I die so hard each time.

01:27:00.560 --> 01:27:03.864 align:middle line:90%


01:27:03.864 --> 01:27:06.696 align:middle line:90%
[VIOLIN PLAYING]

01:27:06.696 --> 01:27:13.520 align:middle line:84%
>> Timothy Leary's last trip
